FBIS3-9357 "dreeu056__a94041" FBIS-EEU-94-056-A Document Type:Daily Report 22 Mar 1994 ANNEX Yugoslavia, Kosovo Money Allocated for Serbian `Colonization' AU2203180494 Tirana ATA in English 1112 GMT 22 Mar 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2203180494 Tirana ATA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tirana, March 22 (ATA) -- The Belgrade's Serbian authorities recently reported they have allocated 400 million DM [German marks] for the construction of buildings and houses for Serbian settlers envisaged to be brought to Kosova. [number indistinct] Albanians have been suspended so far from their jobs and are being replaced by Serbians [word indistinct] in Kosova from Serbia, Bosnia, or Croatia. 300,000 Albanians have immigrated during the recent years and forced by the Serbian repression they have emigrated in Western Europe. There are so far 30,000 Serbian settlers in Kosova and this number is increasing. New settlers, who keep coming to Kosova, have been given houses and agricultural land. The Kosova colonization is laid as primary task in the Milosevic nationalist program for an unique Serbia. Last week, Serbian authorities in Prishtina decided to grant Serbians 50 construction sites.
